<h2>Button</h2>

<p>This library includes modules related to the button user interface element:</p>

<ul class="modules">
    <li><%= DOC.modules.render('Entity/Button') %></li>
    <li><%= DOC.modules.render('Entity/Button/Group') %></li>
</ul>

<h3>Button</h3>

<p>The <code>a</code>, submit/reset/button <code>input</code>, and <code>button</code> tags are the elements semantically best suited to be used as a button. To apply button, simply use the <code>.button</code> class on the element:</p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;a class="button"&gt;&lt;!-- Button Text --&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</pre>
<p><a class="button">Button</a></p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;button class="button"&gt;&lt;!-- Button Text --&gt;&lt;/button&gt;</pre>
<p><button class="button">Button</button></p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;input type="submit" class="button" value="Button Text"&gt;</pre>
<p><input type="submit" class="button" value="Button"></p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;input type="reset" class="button" value="Button Text"&gt;</pre>
<p><input type="reset" class="button" value="Button"></p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;input type="button" class="button" value="Button Text"&gt;</pre>
<p><input type="button" class="button" value="Button"></p>

<h4>Button Sizes</h4>

<p>Three size modifiers <code>.mini</code>, <code>.small</code> and <code>.large</code> may be used upon the button class:</p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;a class="button mini"&gt;&lt;!-- Button Text --&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</pre>
<p><a class="button mini">Mini Button</a></p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;a class="button small"&gt;&lt;!-- Button Text --&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</pre>
<p><a class="button small">Small Button</a></p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;a class="button large"&gt;&lt;!-- Button Text --&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</pre>
<p><a class="button large">Large Button</a></p>

