<h3>Button Groups</h3>

<p>Buttons can be grouped by surrounding a set of <code>.button</code> elements with an element with a <code>.group</code> class:</p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;span class="group"&gt;
    &lt;a class="button"&gt;&lt;!-- 1 --&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;a class="button"&gt;&lt;!-- 2 --&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;a class="button"&gt;&lt;!-- 3 --&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;</pre>

<p>
    <span class="group">
        <a class="button">1</a>
        <a class="button">2</a>
        <a class="button">3</a>
    </span>
</p>

<p>These buttons may also be colored:</p>

<pre class="prettyprint">&lt;span class="group"&gt;
    &lt;a class="button primary"&gt;&lt;!-- 1 --&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;a class="button secondary"&gt;&lt;!-- 2 --&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;a class="button tertiary"&gt;&lt;!-- 3 --&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;</pre>

<p>
    <span class="group">
        <a class="button primary">1</a>
        <a class="button secondary">2</a>
        <a class="button tertiary">3</a>
    </span>
</p>

